UDTCAT
------
udtcat is simple data transfer tool over the reliable UDP-based Data Transfer (UDT) protocol. 

Git: http://github.com/oghazal/udtcat

What is UDT?
------------
UDT is a reliable UDP based application level data transport protocol for distributed data intensive applications over wide area high-speed networks. UDT uses UDP to transfer bulk data with its own reliability control and congestion control mechanisms. The new protocol can transfer data at a much higher speed than TCP does.

http://udt.sourceforge.net/

Installation
------------
udtcat depends on the UDT library, please install the development package of the UDT.

Debain and Ubuntu 
$ sudo   apt-get   update
$ sudo   apt-get   install   build-essential   libudt-dev
$ make 
$ sudo   make   install 

Fedora, Centos, and Red hat

$ sudo   yum   install   make   automake   gcc   gcc-c++   udt-devel
$ make 
$ sudo   make   install

usage examples
--------------
* simple chat

$ udtcat -l     # listen on the default port on machine A
$ udtcat 192.168.100.99     # connect to machine A from machine B

* file transfer 
$ udtcat -l -p 8899 > ~/Downloads/recevied_file.data  # listen on port 8899 on machine A
$ cat ~/Desktop/file.data | udtcat 192.168.100.99 -p 8899  # send the file from machine B to machine A

* like many other tools, udtcat handles SIGUSR1 and prints total sent and received bytes when receiving the signal.
$ killall -SIGUSR1 udcat
